# Cursor Rules Index

Use this file as a lightweight entrypoint only.

## Canonical Source
- Canonical rules live in `.cursor/rules/`.
- Do not duplicate rule content in this file.
- If there is any conflict, `.cursor/rules/` always wins.

## Rule Resolution Order
1. `.cursor/rules/project/active-design-style.md`
2. `.cursor/rules/project/*.md`
3. `.cursor/rules/tech/*.md`
4. `.cursor/rules/general/*.md`
5. `.cursor/rules/design-styles/*.md` (reference library; inactive unless selected)

## What To Load By Context
- Always load all files in `.cursor/rules/general/`.
- Load relevant files from `.cursor/rules/tech/` by language/framework/path.
- Load relevant files from `.cursor/rules/project/` for domain-specific behavior.
- For UI work, always load `.cursor/rules/project/active-design-style.md`.
- Then load only the style file referenced by `STYLE_FILE` in `active-design-style.md`.

## Active Design Style
- Source of truth: `.cursor/rules/project/active-design-style.md`
- Current style is defined there (do not hardcode it here).
- Do not mix multiple design styles unless explicitly requested.

## Maintenance Policy
- Keep this file short and stable.
- Add or edit rule details in `.cursor/rules/` files, not here.
- Update this file only when folder structure or resolution logic changes.
